HEADWORD: attelet
<hw>attelet</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[fr. L.
<ets>hasta</ets>, rod, staff.]</ety> <fld>(Cooking)</fld> <def>a type of
skewer with an ornamental handle which is used for holding foods for
presentation at the table, but not while cooking.</def> <altsp>[formerly
spelled <asp>hatelet</asp>]</altsp> <au>Larousse Gastronomique</au>⟦br⟧
